  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">More coffee with less water - towards a reduction of the blue water footprint in coffee production</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Intensified coffee production in Vietnam &#x96; the second largest coffee producer in the world &#x96; has resulted in declining water availability due to overuse and water mismanagement. Building on earlier successes, this public-private development partnership (PPDP) between the SDC and Nestl&#xE9; commits to a scaling up of water saving practices in the Vietnamese coffee sector. Aligned with the vision of the Coffee Coordinating Board headed by the Vietnamese Ministry of Agriculture, water management in agriculture will be brought to the agenda through a pragmatic showcase PPDP at implementation level.</narrative>
  </description>
